SIMPLE: lifeline
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: lifeline
<hw>lifeline</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The anem given to one
of the creases on the palm; its length is said by palmists to indicate
how long one will live.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> line of life, life line.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A line or rope which raises or lowers a deep-sea
diver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A line from a vessel that people in a body of water
can cling to to save themselves from drowning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lifelong</ent>⟦br⟧
